# This README tells you how to install and use MeCab and konoha mecab bind.
#
# Author: Motoki Yoan (July, 9, 2012)

konoha mecab bind requires followings.
  1. konoha2 (git://github.com/konoha-project/konoha.git)
  2. Mecab   (http://mecab.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/mecab/doc/index.html)

############## 1. GET MeCab ###################

1.1 Download Mecab
  $ wget http://mecab.googlecode.com/files/mecab-0.994.tar.gz
1.2 Download IPA dictionary
  $ wget http://mecab.googlecode.com/files/mecab-ipadic-2.7.0-20070801.tar.gz

############## 2. HOW TO INSTALL ##############

2.1 Install MeCab

  $ cd /path/to/konoha/package/mecab
  $ tar zxvf libs/mecab-xxx.tar.gz
  $ cd mecab-xxx
  $ ./configure --enable-utf8-only
  $ make && sudo make install

2.2 Install IPA dictionary

  $ cd /path/to/konoha/package/mecab
  $ tar zxvf libs/mecab-ipadic-xxx.tar.gz
  $ cd mecab-ipadic-xxx
  $ ./configure --with-charset=utf8
  $ make && sudo make install

2.3 Install konoha MeCab bind.

  $ vi CMakeLists.txt // add mecab package
  $ mkdir build
  $ cd build
  $ cmake .. && make && sudo make install

############## 3. SAMPLES ##############

  $ cd /path/to/konoha/package/mecab/test/Debug
  $ konoha example.k
  $ konoha getNoun.k

